---
let list = [
  { left: 'Individuals and interactions', right: 'processes and tools' },
  { left: 'Working software', right: 'comprehensive documentation' },
  { left: 'Customer collaboration', right: 'contract negotiation' },
  { left: 'Responding to change', right: 'following a plan' },
]
---

<div>
  We are uncovering better ways of developing software by doing it and helping
  others do it. Through this work we have come to value:
</div>

<div class="inline-grid grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr] items-baseline">
  {
    list.map(({ left, right }) => (
      <>
        <span class="text-lg text-green-600 font-semibold text-right">
          {left}
        </span>
        <span class="mx-2 text-sm font-light">over</span>
        <span>{right}</span>
      </>
    ))
  }
</div>

<div>
  That is, while there is value in the items on the right, we value the items
  <span class="text-lg text-green-600 font-semibold">on the left</span> more.
</div>
